        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>What is the difference between common and preferred stock?</summary>
          <p>Common stock gives shareholders voting rights at corporate meetings but puts them last in line for assets if the company goes bankrupt. Preferred stock usually does not offer voting rights but provides a higher claim on earnings and assets, including fixed dividends.</p>
        </details>
